This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on evaluating neural networks based on their similarity to human brain activation patterns. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions unsupervised predictive coding networks, which are commonly studied in the field of neural computing. 

The paper also relates to computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of a metric to evaluate neural networks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper's focus on modeling visual perception and object matching accuracy suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's use of fMRI data suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NI (Neuroscience and Information Theory).
